[DTO] ComboPackDto: comboPackId, name, price, rarity
    stored combo effect bundle
[DTO] EffectDto: effectId, name, css, js
    stored visual effect primitive
[DTO] AppliedEffectDto: effectId
    effect instance with filled-in knobs
[DTO] ComboTierDto: AppliedEffectDto, soundUrl?
    single combo tier with effect and sound
[DTO] AvatarDto: letter?, flair?, letterId?, frameId?, titleId?, emailId?
    embedded player visual identity
[DTO] InventoryDto: itemId(s)
    flat list of owned store item ids
[DTO] EventBindingDto: eventType, gifUrl
    player celebration gif binding
[DTO] BadgeProgressDto: badgeDefId, count
    tracking counter toward badge
[DTO] BCritDto: criteriaSource, fieldKey, criteriaOperator, value, criteriaChain
    single badge filter predicate
[DTO] CoachingActionDto: auditId, managerEmail, managerNotes, addressedAt
    resolved coaching interaction
[DTO] FilterGroupDto: conjunction
    recursive and-or filter node
[DTO] FilterConditionDto: fieldKey, filterOperator, value
    single filter predicate
[DTO] SortCriterionDto: fieldKey, sortOrder
    single sort column specification
[DTO] GroupCriterionDto: fieldKey, groupingMethod
    single group column specification
[DTO] FormulaFieldDto: key, label, expression
    user-defined computed column
[DTO] ReportQueryDto: FilterGroupDto?, FormulaFieldDto(s)?
    embedded query structure
[DTO] ReportOptionsDto: rowHeight?, colorMethod?
    shared report display settings
[DTO] ReportFolderDto: folderId, name, isDefault
    stored report folder
[DTO] CreateFolderDto: name, createdBy
    input for creating a report folder
[DTO] WidgetSlotDto: widgetId, widgetTypeName, title, column, order, span
    positioned widget in dashboard grid
[DTO] QLConfigDto: qlConfigId, name
    stored question lab configuration
[DTO] CreateQLConfigDto: name
    input for creating a ql config
[DTO] CreateQLQuestionDto: qlConfigId, name, text
    input for creating a ql question
[DTO] PromoteQLConfigDto: qlConfigId
    input for promoting ql to production
[DTO] QLTestDto: questionId, snippet, expected
    stored question lab test case
[DTO] QuestionTypeDto: questionTypeName, regex, parserType
    stored question answer validation type
[DTO] FieldDefDto: key, label, fieldType, required
    embedded input field schema
[DTO] SkipRuleDto: questionId, expression, message
    embedded conditional skip logic
[DTO] RagParamsDto: topK, keep, rerank
    embedded per-question rag settings
[DTO] PipelineConfigDto: maxRetries, retryDelaySeconds
    stored pipeline retry settings
[DTO] IdempotencyRecordDto: idempotencyKey, idempotencyState, attempts
    stored lease-based execution record
[DTO] CreateEvtCfgDto: name, trigger, communicationType
    input for creating an event config
[DTO] UpdateGameCfgDto: teamId, enabled?, threshold?, comboTimeoutMs?
    input for updating game settings
[DTO] AppEventDto: eventType, eventPayload
    stored ephemeral per-user event
[DTO] BroadcastEventDto: eventType, triggerEmail, displayName, message?
    stored org-wide announcement event
[DTO] PrefabEventDefDto: eventType, label, description, icon
    pre-defined broadcast event type
[DTO] LeaderboardEntryDto: email, score
    computed ranking entry
[DTO] PublishItemDto: mktItemType, name, code
    input for publishing to marketplace
[DTO] MktItemDto: mktItemId, mktItemType, name
    stored marketplace item
[DTO] InstallItemDto: mktItemId, teamId
    input for installing marketplace item
[DTO] UpdateDashboardDto: dashboardId, WidgetSlotDto(s)?
    input for updating dashboard widgets
[DTO] ShareDashboardDto: dashboardId, sharedEmails
    input for sharing a dashboard

# Auto-Bot V2

Auto-Bot is a call-center audit automation platform
that ingests call recordings, transcribes them,
scores them against configurable question sets using
LLMs with RAG retrieval, and routes results through
human review and appeals. It includes gamification
to engage agents and flexible reporting for
supervisors, analysts, and admins.

## Business Context

Contact centers need quality assurance on agent
calls. Auto-Bot automates the bulk: an LLM listens
to every call, answers compliance and quality
questions, and flags issues. Humans review only
flagged calls, reducing manual audit workload.
Agents appeal decisions they disagree with, and
judges provide independent arbitration.

The platform is multi-tenant. Each organization is
a root team in a nestable hierarchy. A developer
team sits above all orgs for platform admin. Roles
are data-driven (RoleDef), not code enums. Admins
create custom roles with any capability combination.

All entities use Deno KV with soft-delete via
isActive. Sessions and events expire at 24h TTL.
Logging flows to Grafana Cloud Loki via
waitUntil(fetch()).

## Audit Pipeline

Queue-driven with fan-out on Deno Deploy:

1. Batch submitted with config ID and field values.
2. Each record becomes an audit instance.
3. Recording downloaded from recordings service.
4. Transcription produces raw text via speech API.
5. LLM diarization labels speakers.
6. Skip rules evaluated against field values.
7. Questions populated with interpolated fields.
8. Questions fanned out into parallel batches.
   Each batch: RAG retrieval then LLM answering.
9. Atomic counter tracks remaining batches.
10. Finalize aggregates answers, generates feedback,
    appends result with origin: llm.

Retry: maxRetries 5, retryDelaySeconds 10.
Recording failure -> no-recording terminal state.
LLM errors re-enqueued with exponential backoff.

Events are emitted asynchronously via waitUntil()
after each pipeline step completes. The emitEvent
REQ handles matching triggers, evaluating conditions,
rendering payloads, and dispatching notifications.

## Review and Appeals

LLM "No" answers create a ReviewChecklist. Reviewers
claim items with 30-min atomic locks (CAS on
Deno KV). Claim-lock TTL is 30 minutes. If a
reviewer does not decide within the window, the
claim expires and the item returns to the pool.
Decisions: confirm or flip. All decided ->
consolidate into results.push(origin: reviewer).

Agents file appeals on resolved audits. One appeal
per finding per audit. Appeal types: redo,
different-recording, additional-recording, and
upload-recording. AppealChecklist created for judge.
Same claim-lock mechanics with 30-min TTL.
Decisions: uphold or overturn. Judge result is final.

Both paths produce coaching items when final result
has failed questions.

## Provider System

Providers are code-sandbox adapters with built-in
idempotency. send (fire-and-forget) and
guaranteeSend (pessimistic with reconciliation).
Idempoter uses Deno KV atomic ops for lease-based
locking with sha256(code + payload) as key.

ProviderConfigs cascade up the team tree. Service
Bindings wire services to provider fallback chains.
Circuit breakers mark degraded providers. 5xx and
network errors trigger fallback; 4xx does not.

## Gamification

### Dual Currency

totalXp is monotonic and drives level. Earning XP
adds the same amount to both totalXp and
tokenBalance. Spending deducts from tokenBalance
only so level progression is permanent. Levels
are computed from totalXp, not stored.

### Store Items

Nine item types: letter, frame, title, email,
flair, name_color, font, animation, theme. Each
has a price in tokens, an icon, a color, a weight,
a rarity, and an effects array of AppliedEffects.

### Rarity

Seven tiers: common, normal, rare, epic, legendary,
limited, unique. Rarity is cosmetic metadata driving
store presentation. Limited means time-gated and
unique means one-of-a-kind.

### Weight Mapping

Weight maps to border width and font weight. light
= 3px border + 300 font. regular = 4px + 400.
medium = 5px + 500. bold = 6px + 700.

### Effects

Effect is the visual primitive. css and js fields
are sandboxed strings. Knob functions parameterize
effects via knobs.number, knobs.color, knobs.string,
knobs.url. JS runs via Proxy on the real DOM
element with no document or window access. The
create helper builds child elements.

AppliedEffect pairs an effectId with filled-in knob
values. StoreItems embed an effects array of
AppliedEffects.

### ThemeDefs

Full app color scheme with twelve hex properties:
primary, secondary, accent, success, warning, error,
info, background, surface, foreground, muted,
border. Purchased from the store. Equipped via
equippedThemeId on Player. Overrides CSS custom
properties for that user.

### ComboPacks

Combo effect bundles for queue processing. A
ComboPack has consumers, each with tiers and an
onDrop. Each consumer is an independent effect
pipeline running on floating letter elements.

Tiers are indexed by combo count. Combo 1 uses
tiers[0], combo 2 uses tiers[1], and so on. When
count exceeds tiers.length, it clamps to the last
tier. Each ComboTier pairs an AppliedEffect with an
optional soundUrl.

onDrop fires when comboTimeoutMs expires without a
new audit. comboTimeoutMs is set in GameCfgDto per
team. Combos escalate as the agent resolves audits
in succession.

### Badges

Seven categories: milestone, speed, streak, combo,
level, quality, special. BadgeDef has filter
criteria, an increment expression, and a threshold.
Criteria use source (field or result), key, operator
(=== !== >= <= > <), value, and chain (and or).
Evaluation is left-to-right. And groups must all
pass; or starts a new group.

Increment expression defaults to 1 per event.
Custom increments allow cumulative tracking like
fields.wgsRevenue. When BadgeProgress.count reaches
threshold, the badge moves to earnedBadges with
timestamp and xpReward is granted.

Evaluation triggers: audit.instance.resolved,
audit.result.appended.reviewer,
audit.result.appended.judge, coaching.completed,
player.levelUp.

### Avatar

Five equip slots: letterId (letter), frameId
(frame), titleId (title), emailId (email), flairId
(flair). Each slot references a StoreItem ID from
inventory. The letter and flair fields hold the
display values derived from equipped items.

### Event Bindings

Players choose celebration GIFs per event type.
When the event fires and matches a binding, the
client plays the GIF as an overlay.

### Day Streaks

Consecutive active days. An active day is any day
with at least one audit resolved. Missed day resets
dayStreak to 0. Fires player.streakIncremented and
player.streakBroken respectively.

### Leaderboards

Computed rankings of users by metric: decisions,
flipRate, speed, xp, streak. Scoped by role
(reviewer, judge, agent) and team permissions.
Displayed via leaderboard dashboard widgets.

## Events and Notifications

### AppEvent

Per-user ephemeral event with 24h TTL. Delivered
via SSE stream. Used for real-time UI updates,
toast notifications, badge ticks, combo triggers.

### BroadcastEvent

Org-wide announcement with 24h TTL. Carries
triggerEmail, displayName, message, and animationId.
Drives the gamification feed on dashboards.
PrefabEventDef provides pre-defined broadcast types
with label, description, icon, and defaultMessage
template. Supervisors subscribe to prefab events
per team.

### Message

Persistent direct message between two users. No
TTL. Carries fromEmail, toEmail, body, timestamp,
and read flag.

### EventConfig

Reactive automation. trigger is a dot-scoped pattern
string supporting wildcards like audit.instance.*.
fieldFilter lists field keys that must change; empty
means any change fires. conditions is a FilterGroup
(reuses the reports filter model) evaluating
eventPayload. payloadTemplate renders via the
expression engine. Delivery goes through the
CommunicationProvider interface selecting webhook,
email, chat, or sse.

Flow: event emitted via emit() -> match trigger ->
check fieldFilter -> evaluate conditions -> render
payloadTemplate -> dispatch via communication
provider. Dispatch happens in waitUntil() and does
not block the response.

### Event Catalog

AuditConfig: audit.config.created, modified,
deleted, versionPublished. AuditQuestion:
audit.question.created, modified, deleted,
testPassed, testFailed. AuditInstance:
audit.instance.created, transcribing, transcribed,
transcriptionFailed, asking, completed, failed,
retrying, resolved. AuditResult:
audit.result.appended.llm, .reviewer, .judge.
Appeal: appeal.filed, assigned, decided.
Coaching: coaching.pending, completed. Team:
team.created, modified, deleted, memberAdded,
memberRemoved, leaderChanged. RoleDef:
role.created, modified, deleted. User:
user.created, modified, deactivated, reactivated,
passwordChanged, login, loginFailed. Session:
session.created, expired. Dashboard:
dashboard.created, modified, shared, deleted.
Report: report.created, modified, deleted. Player:
player.xpEarned, xpSpent, levelUp,
streakIncremented, streakBroken. Badge:
badge.earned, progressUpdated. Store:
store.itemPurchased, themeEquipped,
comboPackEquipped. Message: message.sent, read.
Broadcast: broadcast.saleCompleted, perfectScore,
levelUp. EventConfig: eventConfig.created, modified,
deleted, triggered, deliveryFailed. Schedule:
schedule.report. Provider: provider.created,
modified, deleted. ProviderConfig:
providerConfig.created, modified, deactivated,
reactivated. ServiceBinding:
serviceBinding.created, modified, deleted,
fallbackTriggered, circuitBreakerOpened,
circuitBreakerClosed, referenceOrphaned. Generic:
record.created, modified, deleted. Unscoped:
breakingChange.

## Reports

### Report Types

Five types: table (rows and columns), chart (bar,
line, or pie), calendar (date-based event view),
summary (aggregated metrics with optional pivots),
timeline (horizontal time-based track view).

### ReportQuery

Embedded in Report. Contains filter (FilterGroup),
sortBy (SortCriterion array), groupBy
(GroupCriterion array), and formulaFields
(FormulaField array). All optional.

### FilterGroup

Recursive AND/OR structure. conjunction selects how
conditions combine. Conditions can contain nested
FilterGroups for arbitrary depth. Reused by
EventConfig.conditions with same evaluation logic.

### Filter Operators

14 operators: equals, notEquals, contains,
notContains, startsWith, endsWith, greaterThan,
lessThan, greaterOrEqual, lessOrEqual, in, notIn,
isEmpty, isNotEmpty.

### Grouping Methods

Five methods: exact (one group per unique value),
date-day (by calendar day), date-week (by week),
date-month (by month), range (numeric ranges).

### Evaluation Order

1. Fetch data within viewer permission scope.
2. Evaluate FormulaFields per row.
3. Apply FilterGroup including formula filters.
4. Apply SortCriteria.
5. Apply GroupCriteria.
6. Pass to type-specific renderer.

FormulaFields are available to all downstream
operations. Filters apply before grouping.

### Scheduled Reports

Reports can be triggered on a schedule via
EventConfig listening to schedule.report. The
event system renders the report and delivers it
through the configured communication provider.

## Dashboard

### DashboardPage

Per-user per-role dashboard. ownerId null means
system default. Copy-on-first-access: when a user
first visits Dashboard with no personal page for
their role, the system default is deep-cloned with
ownerId set to their email. After that, changes to
the system default do not propagate.

### WidgetSlot

Column-based grid layout. Each widget has column
(horizontal placement), order (vertical position),
and span (columns wide). Default is 3 columns on
desktop. Narrow viewports stack vertically.

### Widget Types

Eight types: report (embedded report), text (static
or dynamic with expression interpolation),
button-bar (action buttons), link-bar (navigation
links), search (scoped search input), reports-list
(browsable saved reports), leaderboard (ranked user
list), embed (sandboxed iframe).

### Sharing

Users share dashboards by adding emails to
sharedWith. Recipients get read-only views. If a
recipient wants to customize, they clone it via
copy-on-first-access and own their copy. Removing
an email from sharedWith revokes access immediately
but cloned copies remain.

### Sidebar

Computed from session capabilities at login. Not
stored. Collapsed state is a thin accent line
(3-4px) from the user's ThemeDef accent color.
Expanded state overlays from the left edge showing
tabs. Dashboard tab is always first. Remaining tabs
derive from capabilities array order.

## Question Lab

### Workflow

QLConfig groups QLQuestions under development.
Each QLQuestion has a text with variable
placeholders, an optional autoYesExp for auto-yes
expressions, and version history tracking every
edit. QLTests provide snippet and expected pairs
for validation.

### Testing

Run a test: RAG retrieval plus LLM answering
against the snippet. Compare result to expected.
Pass/fail and LLM reasoning stored on the test.
Tests are quality tools, not deployment gates.

### Promotion

When satisfied, promote QLConfig to a production
AuditConfig version. The promoteQLConfig REQ loads
the QLConfig, converts it to an AuditConfigDto, and
saves the new config version.

## Audit Template

### AuditConfig Versioning

uuid is stable across edits. version increments on
each edit. configId is the composite key
uuid:-:version used as the KV key. Old versions are
never deleted so AuditInstances can resolve the
exact config they ran against.

### AuditQuestion

Fields: questionText (LLM prompt with expression
interpolation), header (UI display template),
expectedAnswer (correct answer for scoring),
questionType (references QuestionType by name),
ragParams (embedded RagRetrieveParams).

### QuestionType

Defines answer parsing. Fields: name (e.g. yes-no),
regex (validation pattern), parser (bool, int,
float, or string coercion), schema (JSON Schema
for downstream validation). Flow: raw answer ->
regex check -> parser coercion -> schema validation.

### FieldDef

Input field schema. Fields: key (identifier), label
(display name), fieldType (input type), required
(mandatory flag). Can include default and options.
Embedded in AuditConfig.fieldDefs array.

### SkipRule

Expression-driven conditional question removal.
Fields: questionId (which question to skip),
expression (evaluated against fieldMap), message
(reason text). Embedded in AuditConfig.skip array.

### RagRetrieveParams

Per-question RAG settings. Fields: topK (max
results), keep (min relevance score), mmrLambda
(diversity weight, 0=diverse, 1=relevant),
hybridAlpha (keyword vs semantic balance), rerank
(whether to re-rank after retrieval). Different
questions need different retrieval strategies.

### PipelineConfig

Operational tuning separate from audit definition.
Fields: maxRetries (retry limit), retryDelaySeconds
(delay between retries). Changing pipeline settings
does not bump the audit config version.

## Roles and Capabilities

### RoleDef

Fields: name, level, capabilities array, permissions
array, isActive. Belongs to the org root team. One
set of RoleDefs per org.

### Level Hierarchy

Level 0 is developer (platform-level, above all
orgs). Level 1 is admin (org-level). Level 2 and
above are team-level roles. Lower number means more
access. You see yourself plus anyone with a higher
level number. Peers cannot see each other.

### Default Roles

Six defaults: developer (level 0, full platform
access), admin (level 1, org management), supervisor
(level 2, team audits coaching reports), judge
(level 2, appeals queue), analyst (level 2, reports
and configs), agent (level 3, audit queue store
appeals profile).

### Custom Roles

Admins create RoleDefs with custom names, chosen
levels, and specific capability and permission sets.
The system treats them identically to defaults.
Capabilities are strings mapping to sidebar tabs
and routes. No hard-coded role-to-function mappings.

### Caching

RoleDef fields are cached on UserRecord (roleId,
role, level, capabilities, permissions) and
snapshotted to Session at login. A RoleDef change
triggers fan-out write to all referencing
UserRecords. Existing sessions see old capabilities
until 24h TTL expires or re-login.

## Marketplace

### Item Types

Eleven types: effects, functions, themes, widgets,
report types, store items, badge definitions, email
templates, calculated fields, validators, condition
functions.

### Sandbox Model

All marketplace items are sandboxed string functions
using the same Proxy-based model as Effects. No
document, no window, no DOM access. Query utility
available scoped to user permissions. Timeout on
execution for slow code.

### Publish and Install

Developers build JSON packages and publish to the
marketplace. Admins install items per org. Open
publishing is safe because the sandbox is airtight.

## Idempotency

### Idempoter API

from(options) binds schema, lease timeout, and
reconciliation callback. defineScope(scope, keys)
binds the scope and key fields for hashing.
execute(obj, fn) runs the side-effecting function.
mark(key, receipt?) updates record state externally.

### IdempotencyRecord

Fields: key (sha256 of scope + sorted key-value
pairs), state (locked, succeeded, unknown, failed),
lockedUntil (lease expiry timestamp), attempts
(execution attempt count).

### State Machine

locked -> succeeded (fn returns). locked -> unknown
(fn throws). unknown -> succeeded (reconcile returns
receipt). unknown -> failed (reconcile returns null).
unknown -> unknown (reconcile throws). Lease
atomicity guaranteed by Deno KV CAS primitives.

### Reconciliation

Callback injected at construction. Returns receipt
means side effect happened, record moves to
succeeded. Returns null means did not happen, moves
to failed. Throws means vendor unreachable, stays
unknown. Triggered on re-execute of unknown keys.

## Expression Language

### Syntax

Variables: {{currentUser}}, {{record.fieldName}}.
Functions: functionName(arg1, arg2). Nesting
supported: llm('prompt', extractFailedQuestions(
audits({{currentUser}}), 10)). Literals: strings
and numbers.

### Context

Depends on use-site. Email/webhook/chat: event,
currentUser, record, field values. Badge increment:
fields.*, result. Skip rules: fields.*.

### Function Types

Data fetchers: audits(user), appeals(user),
scores(user, configId). Transformers:
extractFailedQuestions(audits, limit), average(),
count(), latest(). AI: llm(prompt, ...context).
Helpers: string, math, and date utilities.

## Services

Named app functions bound to providers via
ServiceBinding:

- audit-questions: bulk yes/no via cheap fast LLM.
- transcription: speech-to-text via Whisper or
  AssemblyAI.
- expression-eval: expression engine via powerful
  LLM.
- email-sending: outbound email via SES, SendGrid,
  or Postmark.
- file-storage: binary storage via S3 or GCS.
- recordings: call recording download from Genie,
  direct upload, or any recording provider.
- queue: async pipeline step orchestration via
  QStash, SQS, or any queue provider.
- messaging: in-app message delivery resolving to
  Slack, Teams, or in-app chat.
- notification-delivery: outbound dispatch for
  EventConfig actions receiving rendered payloads
  and sending via the bound provider.

## Storage

Deno KV for all entities. Soft-delete via isActive.
Sessions 24h TTL. Events 24h TTL. Logging to
Grafana Cloud Loki via waitUntil(fetch()).
